## Completeness and the addition of rules

After we covered the introduction and elimination rules for the connectives, we kept on adding rules to our deductive system like EFSQ and DN, even when these departed more and more from the guiding idea of natural deduction that the only rules are those that allow for the introduction and elimination of a symbol. But how do we know when we are "done" adding rules?

Kleene's idea was that the Completeness Theorem tells us this, since given completeness any valid argument is already derivable from these rules:[^1]

